## Format Examples

### Example 1: Agent Finding Contradicts Prior Work

```
[2026-04-15 14:32] AGENT-CONTRADICTION: memory/reference_psychology_optimized_ctas_by_industry.md
Agent: general-purpose-agent-1 2026-04-15 HIGH
Old Finding: "Any CTA works fine, psychology doesn't matter"
New Finding: "Binary CTAs get 13x more meetings than open-ended CTAs"
Reasoning: Old finding had no source; new finding backed by 304K email study (Instantly.ai)
Sources:
  - Old: reference_psychology_optimized_ctas_by_industry.md v1.0 (2026-04-01)
  - New: .claude/agent-exits/2026-04-15_general-purpose-agent-1_psychology-cta-framework.md
Exit Log: .claude/agent-exits/2026-04-15_general-purpose-agent-1_psychology-cta-framework.md
Status: awaiting_review
Recommendation: Adopt new finding (HIGH confidence + research-backed). Replace old statement with Agent 1's finding. Update reference file v1.0 → v1.1.
```

### Example 2: Agent Finding Augments (Not Contradicts) Prior Work

If an agent finds "Scarcity principle works specifically for Logistics" but the old finding was "Psychology principles work in general," this is not a contradiction—it's clarification. /save would log this as AUGMENTATION, not AGENT-CONTRADICTION:

```
[2026-04-15 15:45] AGENT-AUGMENTATION: memory/reference_psychology_optimized_ctas_by_industry.md
Agent: general-purpose-agent-2 2026-04-15 MEDIUM
Extends: "Psychology principles work in general"
Refined Finding: "Scarcity principle specifically works for Logistics (binary choice + urgency window)"
Evidence: Framework theory + industry-specific CTA variants created
Sources:
  - Prior: reference_psychology_optimized_ctas_by_industry.md v1.0
  - New: .claude/agent-exits/2026-04-15_general-purpose-agent-2_logistics-cta-variants.md
Exit Log: .claude/agent-exits/2026-04-15_general-purpose-agent-2_logistics-cta-variants.md
Status: resolved
Action: Added to reference file as industry-specific variant (v1.0 → v1.1)
```

### Example 3: Sourced from Source File Upload (Legacy)

```
[2026-04-14 09:20] CONFLICT: memory/project_internship_2026.md
